---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../config";
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Pontoon Picnic Table | {siteConfig.name}</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A floating picnic table pontoon built under $100 and tested on the Salt River."
    />
  </head>

  <body class="bg-background text-foreground">

    <Header />

    <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
      <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-8">
        <header class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-blue-500">
            Project
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-100">
            Pontoon Picnic Table
          </h1>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-400">
            A DIY floating picnic table built with 55-gallon HDPE barrels and a
            reinforced frame, designed to carry a full picnic setup and a group
            of friends down the Salt River.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Overview</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            This project started as a challenge: build a stable, river-ready
            picnic platform on a student budget. I designed and built a pontoon
            using reclaimed 55-gallon HDPE barrels as flotation and a reinforced
            frame to support a full-size picnic table and multiple passengers.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            The pontoon completed a full Salt River run (Water Users â†’ Exit 4)
            carrying four people. It handled rocks, shallow water, and light
            impacts with only minor dents to the barrels and no structural
            failures. Total build cost stayed under $100.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">My Role</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Designed the frame, barrel layout, and tie-down system.</li>
            <li>Cut, drilled, and assembled the structure using basic shop tools.</li>
            <li>Managed sourcing and budgeting to stay under a $100 cap.</li>
            <li>Planned and executed the first on-river test with a full crew.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">What I Learned</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Practical buoyancy, stability, and weight distribution tradeoffs.</li>
            <li>How to design for abuse: rocks, scraping, and real-world misuse.</li>
            <li>Balancing cost, safety, and fun under tight constraints.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Tech & Skills</h2>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-800 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Welding / Fabrication
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-800 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Rapid Prototyping
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-800 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Project Management
            </span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-800 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-200">
              Design Under Constraints
            </span>
          </div>
        </section>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
